{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.32",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 32 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:1",
      "text": "Have they made you ruler of a feast? Don’t be lifted up. Be among them as one of them. Take care of them first, and then sit down.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:2",
      "text": "And when you have done all your duties, take your place, that you may be gladdened on their account, and receive a wreath for your good service.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:3",
      "text": "Speak, you who are older, for it’s your right, but with sound knowledge; and don’t interrupt the music.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:4",
      "text": "Don’t pour out talk where there is a performance of music. Don’t display your wisdom at the wrong time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:5",
      "text": "As a ruby signet in a setting of gold, so is a music concert at a wine banquet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:6",
      "text": "As an emerald signet in a work of gold, so is musical melody with pleasant wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:7",
      "text": "Speak, young man, if you are obliged to, but no more than twice, and only if asked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:8",
      "text": "Sum up your speech, many things in few words. Be as one who knows and yet holds his tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:9",
      "text": "When among great men, don’t behave as their equal. When another is speaking, don’t babble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:10",
      "text": "Lightning speeds before thunder. Approval goes before one who is modest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:11",
      "text": "Rise up in good time, and don’t be last. Go home quickly and don’t loiter",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:12",
      "text": "Amuse yourself there and do what is in your heart. Don’t sin by proud speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:13",
      "text": "For these things bless your Maker, who gives you to drink freely of his good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:14",
      "text": "He who fears the Lord will receive discipline. Those who seek him early will find favor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:15",
      "text": "He who seeks the law shall be filled with it, but the hypocrite will stumble at it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:16",
      "text": "Those who fear the Lord will find true judgment, and will kindle righteous acts like a light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:17",
      "text": "A sinful man shuns reproof, and will find a judgment according to his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:18",
      "text": "A sensible person won’t neglect a thought. An insolent and proud man won’t crouch in fear, even after he has done a thing by himself without counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:19",
      "text": "Do nothing without counsel, but when you have acted, don’t regret it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:20",
      "text": "Don’t go in a way of conflict. Don’t stumble in stony places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:21",
      "text": "Don’t be overconfident on a smooth road.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:22",
      "text": "Beware of your own children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:23",
      "text": "In every work guard your own soul, for this is the keeping of the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.32.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:24",
      "text": "He who believes the law gives heed to the commandment. He who trusts in the Lord will suffer no loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
